1 1. “Bulk milk hauler/sampler” means any person collecting
2 official samples who may transport raw milk from a farm or raw milk
3 products to or from a milk plant, receiving station, or transfer
4 station and has in his or her possession a permit from any state to
5 sample these products;
6 2. “Dairy farm” means any premises owned or operated by a “milk
7 producer” milk producer where one or more cows or goats hooved
8 mammals are kept, and from which a part or all of the milk or milk
9 products is sold or offered for sale;
10 3. “Goat milk” means the lacteal secretion, practically free
11 from colostrum, obtained by the complete milking of one or more
12 healthy goats;
13 4. “Grade A milk and milk products” means milk and milk
14 products at any stage from production through pasteurization and
15 packaging, that are of the minimum quality and are produced, hauled,
16 processed and distributed under conditions which meet the
17 requirements of the Oklahoma Milk and Milk Products Act;
18 5. 4. “Inhibitor” means any chemical or antibiotic substance
19 which inhibits or retards the growth of bacteria in milk;
20 6. 5. “Milk” means the lacteal secretion, practically free from
21 colostrum, obtained by the complete milking of one or more healthy
22 cows hooved mammals, which contains not less than eight and one-
23 fourth percent (8 1/4%) milk solids-not-fat and not less than three
24 and one-fourth percent (3 1/4%) milk fat. The term “milk” milk
