1 shal l include goat hooved mammal milk, fluid market milk, and milk
2 products for the purpose of distribution to the consumer, and may
3 contain optional ingredients defined by the State Board of
4 Agriculture and shall include ungraded and Grade A milk;
5 7. 6. “Milk contact surface” means any pipe, tank, equipment,
6 or facility which contacts or may contact milk during the producing,
7 transporting, processing, or distributing of milk and milk products;
8 8. 7. “Milk distribution center” means any premises, owned or
9 operated by a “milk distributor” milk distributor, which distributes
10 and sells or offers to sell milk and milk products but does not
11 include an establishment which sells or offers to sell Grade A milk
12 and milk products at retail;
13 9. 8. “Milk facility” means the producing, processing,
14 transporting, or distributing premises and facilities which operate
15 under an appropriate and valid permit issued by the Commissioner, in
16 compliance with the Oklahoma Milk and Milk Products Act and the
17 rules of the Board;
18 10. 9. “Milk fat” or “butter fat” means the fat of milk;
19 11. 10. “Milk plant” means any premises owned or operated by a
20 “milk processor” milk processor where milk or milk products are
21 collected, manufactured, processed, pasteurized, bottled, stored, or
22 prepared for distribution for commercial purposes including, but not
23 limited to, a receiving or transfer station;
24
