1 12. 11. “Milk products” means those products produced or
2 obtained from milk or any component or product of milk and defined
3 by the Board, including Grade A milk products, ungraded raw milk,
4 and ungraded milk products;
5 13. 12. “Milk tank truck cleaning facility” means any premises
6 or establishment, separate from a milk plant, receiving station, or
7 transfer station, where a milk tank truck is cleaned and sanitized;
8 14. 13. “Milk tank truck driver” means any person transporting
9 raw or pasteurized milk products between a milk plant, receiving
10 station, or transfer station;
11 15. 14. “Milk transportation company” means any person
12 responsible for a milk tank truck;
13 16. 15. “Pasteurized milk” means Grade A raw milk which has
14 been pasteurized and stored in accordance with the chemical,
15 bacteriological, and temperature standards required by the Board;
16 17. 16. “Receiving station” means any premises where raw milk
17 is received, collected, handled, stored, or cooled and prepared for
18 further transporting;
19 18. 17. “Retail food store” means any establishment which
20 offers for retail sale packaged or bulk food goods for human
21 consumption;
22 19. 18. “Transfer station” means any establishment or premises
23 where milk or milk products are transferred directly from one milk
24 tank truck to another; and
