5 SECTION 3. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-415, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 7-415. A. A fee of one cent ($0.01) two cents ($0.02)
8 shall be assessed on each one hundred (100) pounds of raw milk
9 produced in this state. Each co-op, marketing agent, or processing
10 plant where the raw milk is not collected by a co-op or marketing
11 agent, doing business in Oklahoma this state shall pay the fees each
12 calendar month to the Commissioner of Agriculture to be credited to
13 the Milk and Milk Products Inspection Revolving Fund of the State
14 Treasury.
15 B. There is hereby assessed a fee of one cent ($0.01) two cents
16 ($0.02) on each one hundred (100) pounds of Grade A milk or milk
17 products processed or offered for retail sale in Oklahoma this
18 state. Each milk plant doing business in Oklahoma this state shall
19 pay the fees each calendar month to the Commissioner to be credited
20 to the Milk and Milk Products Inspection Revolving Fund of the State
21 Treasury.
22 C. A fee of two cents ($0.02) shall be assessed on each one
23 hundred (100) pounds of milk or milk products produced or processed
24 in another state and imported into Oklahoma shall be the same amount
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2071 SFLR Page 5
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 asse ssed on milk or milk products shipped to that state from
2 Oklahoma this state. The person shipping or causing the shipment of
3 milk or milk products shall be responsible for paying the fees semi-
4 annually on January 1 and July 1 of each year to the Commissioner
5 and such fees shall be credited to the Milk and Milk Products
6 Inspection Revolving Fund of the State Treasury.
7 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 7-421, is
8 amended to read as follows:
9 Section 7-421. The Oklahoma State Department of Agriculture,
10 Food, and Forestry is hereby designated as the official state agency
11 of this state for purposes of cooperating with and implementing the
12 dairy inspection and grading program under the jurisdiction of the
13 United States Department of Agriculture, the United States
14 Department of Health and Human Services, the United States Public
15 Health Service, and the United States Food and Drug Administration.
16 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
17 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
